    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks @hkdobrev for the feedback. Right now, this is not possible as part of instantsearch.js but we can definitely work something out to have an option. In the meantime, you could monkeypatch the widget and check the number of pages, like so:\n\n``` js\nvar container = document.querySelector('#pagination');\nvar paginationWidget = instantsearch.widgets.pagination({container: container});\nvar oldRender = paginationWidget.render;\npaginationWidget.render = function(params) {\n  var currentState = params.results;\n  if(currentState.nbPages===0) container.style.display='none';\n  else container.style.display = 'block';\n  oldRender.call(this, arguments);\n}\nsearch.addWidget(paginationWidget);\n```\n",
